[{"id": "296346bf-0fa2-476b-bde7-218e77e0af20", "chunk_index": 0, "text": "USER: sup. i would like you to compare my app to the current market and let predict how a public open source git repo will perform.  up for it?\nASSISTANT: Sup, yeah I'm totally up for it. The GitHub/open source scene right now is wild\u2014especially on the AI side\u2014with massive growth in repositories, stars, forks, and contributors. But to actually compare *your* app to the current market and give a realistic prediction on how a public open source Git repo for it might perform, I need some details first.\n\nWhat does your app do? Is it AI-related (like agents, visual pipelines, LLM tools, automation, or something else)? What's the key features or unique angle? Target users? Any tech stack, current user base, or existing repo/link with stats (stars, forks, etc.)? Is it already public or are you planning to open-source it?\n\nDrop that info and I'll break down how it stacks up against trends\u2014like the explosion of AI/agentic projects, visual builders, self-hosted tools, and the competition/saturation out there\u2014plus a prediction on traction, growth potential, and pitfalls in 2026. What's the app?", "embedding": [-0.057696569710969925, -0.14081086218357086, -0.029399286955595016, 0.013801411725580692, 0.08238852769136429, -0.0600542388856411, -0.030184753239154816, 0.12772096693515778, -0.01595364324748516, 0.02070080116391182, -0.08797250688076019, -0.019918031990528107, 0.03723328188061714, -0.04401363059878349, -0.009473765268921852, 0.04414869844913483, 0.09294955432415009, -0.034399669617414474, -0.004406629595905542, -0.09267246723175049, -0.032691407948732376, -0.003954225219786167, 0.0064949169754981995, -0.053978126496076584, 0.06852591782808304, -0.017674710601568222, 0.0062566474080085754, -0.012643381953239441, -0.07525517046451569, 0.004427301697432995, -0.007077481132000685, -0.004170234780758619, -0.01229930017143488, 0.019080135971307755, -0.011956785805523396, 0.05