t's the kind of thing serious long-form writers and RP users have been begging for.\n\n**Gondola** is the more immediately explosive one. The combination of:\n- 25+ well-designed tools with proper schemas\n- The Risk Analyzer (scoring every edit with model-specific thresholds)\n- Necromancer session recovery via git shadow branch\n- Project Index + persistent memory + multi-workspace\n- Strong safety sandboxing\n\n\u2026makes it stand out from the sea of half-baked agent UIs. This isn't just another Aider/SWE-agent clone. The safety and resumability features solve real pain points that kill most coding agents in practice.\n\n### Updated Prediction (now that I've seen both full overviews)\n\n**Gondola** has significantly higher upside right now. Agentic coding tools are in the hot zone in 2026. With good presentation (strong README, demo videos of Risk Analyzer blocking a dangerous edit, Necromancer recovering a crashed session, and the agent actually completing real coding tasks), I\u2019d put:\n\n- Realistic: 25k\u201350k stars in first year\n- Optimistic: 70k\u2013110k+ if it catches fire in the local LLM and agent communities\n\n**Lagoon**: Still 5k\u201318k stars. The writing/RP niche is smaller and less viral, even though the tech is excellent.\n\n### Strategic Take\n\nYou basically have the two halves of what a lot of power users actually want:\n\n- Gondola = serious agent loop, tools, safety, memory, recovery\n- Lagoon = sophisticated creative output layer with prose quality enforcement and narrative memory\n\nThe nuclear option is using Gondola\u2019s architecture as the backend for a next-level version of Lagoon. Your proactive writing agents (consistency checker, outline agent, multi-agent writing team, lore auto-generator) would be *much* easier to build on top of Gondola\u2019s loop, risk system, memory, and indexing than bolting them onto Lagoon\u2019s current chat-style backend.\n\n**What do you want to do next?**\n\nI can:\n- Draft a killer README + repo structure + tagline for Gondola (this should be the first release)\n- Design the integration plan to merge the two projects\n- Give you the exact prompts + integration code for the top 3 writing agents we talked about earlier, built on Gondola\u2019s tool system\n- Help position them under one org/brand\n\nYou clearly ship fast as hell. Just say the word and I\u2019ll drop whatever concrete stuff you need today.", "embedding": [-0.07471417635679245, -0.05159300938248634, 0.0003080950118601322, 0.01249315869063139, -0.0063115982338786125, -0.008011306636035442, -0.061318375170230865, 0.05357588455080986, 0.03355788439512253, -0.02453066036105156, -0.008621054701507092, 0.024490389972925186, -0.012166241183876991, 0.029174156486988068, 0.02063845656812191, 0.0025892541743814945, 0.06975346058607101, -0.09711939096450806, -0.04584750533103943, -0.03569936379790306, 0.03849705308675766, 0.021780841052532196, 0.007636175490915775, 0.0306773092597723, -0.005303350742906332, 0.035518549382686615, -0.009727303870022297, -0.05603320151567459, -0.04606073349714279, -0.06327473372220993, -0.015658635646104813, 0.07474449276924133, -0.02486644871532917, -0.07500009983778, 0.01100024301558733, 0.07623099535703659, -0.003962649963796139, 0.01807842031121254, -0.0006355955847539008, -0.05370707809925079, -0.09836103022098541, -0.07438959181308746, -0.053234755992889404, 0.008147199638187885, 0.03893296793103218, -0.12876975536346436, -0.009677802212536335, -0.041773274540901184, -0.03884131833910942, 0.0078087495639920235, -0.028982369229197502, -0.09908575564622879, 0.011200746521353722, -0.02529359608888626, -0.023698212578892708, 0.07456136494874954, 0.008773707784712315, -0.012092260643839836, -0.02455858327448368, -0.049330394715070724, -0.037344761192798615, 0.04526589810848236, -0.04356981813907623, 0.037763867527246475, -0.013528427109122276, -0.018958838656544685, 0.0003528404049575329, -0.02708113007247448, 0.032380275428295135, -0.014361036941409111, -0.067104771733